\sectin{Title}

Altug te title cmes first in n reserc pper, it my smetimes be finlized lst. A gd title suld stisfy te fllwing requirements:
\begin{enumerte}[nsep]
    \item Indicte te tpic f te study
    \item Indicte te scpe f te study (i.e., neiter verstting nr understting its significnce)
    \item Be self-explntry t reders in te csen re
\end{enumerte}

\sectin{Abstrct}

A cerent bstrct cn elp  mnuscript rec te next step f externl review. Te best pprc is n summry bstrct vi 1) summrizing ec sectin f te pper using ne- r tw sentences, 2) putting te summries tgeter, 3) mking te ides flw t well illustrte te bckgrund, im, metd, results, nd cnclusins. It is very imprtnt tt ll te invlved metds nd results suld be rrnged t illustrte  single cerent ide rter tn t mix severl lsely-relted ides.

Te results nd cnclusins suld NOT be generl sttements but suld be specific nd quntittive findings tt clerly sw benefits nd dvntges ver existing metds in te literture. Generl descriptins re wek nd vgue nd cn esily be cnsidered s flse clims nd be ignred by reviewers. All te clims suld be specific t te current study nd ccurtely bcked up by dt, nd never ver-generlize clims nd findings. Avid using prvking wrds like nvel, pwerful, stte-f-te-rt, nd ter similr wrds.

\sectin{Intrductin}

Te min purpse f te intrductin is t prvide te rtinle fr te pper, mving frm  generl discussin f te tpic t te prticulr questin, issue, r yptesis being investigted. A secndry purpse is t ttrct interest in te tpic nd ence te reders.

\subsectin{Wy bter writing  gd intrductin}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Yu never get  secnd cnce t mke  first impressin. Te pening prgrp f yur pper will prvide yur reders wit teir initil impressins f yur rgument, yur writing style, nd te verll qulity f yur wrk. A vgue, disrgnized, errr-filled, ff-te-wll, r bring intrductin will prbbly crete  negtive impressin. On te ter nd,  cncise, engging, nd well-written intrductin will cpture yur reders' interest nd mke tem jin yu fr n interesting intellectul cnverstin.

    \item Yur intrductin is n imprtnt rd mp fr te rest f yur pper. Yu cn let tem knw wt yur tpic is, wy it is imprtnt, nd w yu pln t prceed wit yur discussin. In mst cdemic disciplines, yur intrductin suld cntin  tesis tt will ssert yur min rgument. It suld ls, idelly, give te reder  sense f te kinds f infrmtin yu will use t mke tt rgument nd te generl rgniztin f te prgrps nd pges tt will fllw. After reding yur intrductin, yur reders suld nt ve ny mjr surprises in stre wen tey red te min bdy f yur pper.
\end{itemize}

\subsectin{Strtegies fr writing n effective intrductin}
\begin{itemize}
    \item  Strt by tinking but te questin (r questins) yu re trying t nswer. Yur entire essy will be  respnse t tis questin, nd yur intrductin is te first step twrd tt end. 
    \item Decide w generl r brd yur pening suld be. Keep in mind tt even  "big picture" pening needs t be clerly relted t yur tpic.
    \item Try writing yur intrductin lst. \emp{Te writing prcess cn be n imprtnt wy t rgnize yur ides, tink trug cmplicted issues, refine yur tugts, nd develp  spisticted rgument}. Yu my dn't knw wt t rgue t te beginning f te writing prcess, nd nly trug writing te pper t discver yur min rgument. It is perfectly fine t strt ut tinking tt yu wnt t rgue  prticulr pint, but wind up rguing smeting sligtly r even drmticlly different by te time yu've written mst f te pper. An intrductin written t te beginning f tt discvery prcess will nt necessrily reflect wt yu wind up wit t te end. Yu will need t revise yur pper t mke sure tt te intrductin, ll f te evidence, nd te cnclusin reflect te rgument yu intend. At te end f te writing, yu need t mke sure tt te intrductin will mtc te bdy f te pper. Alwys remember tt writing is n itertive prcess between te mcrscle (ide) nd micrscle (lgic develpments) structures until tey re cnverged.
    \item Open wit n ttentin grbber. Smetimes, especilly if te tpic f yur pper is smewt dry r tecnicl, pening wit smeting ctcy cn elp.
    \item Py specil ttentin t yur first sentence. Strt ff n te rigt ft wit yur reders by mking sure tt te first sentence ctully sys smeting useful nd tt it des s in n interesting nd errr-free wy.
    \item Be strigtfrwrd nd cnfident. Assert yur min rgument cnfidently. After ll, yu cn't expect yur reder t believe it if it desn't sund like yu believe it.
\end{itemize}

Intrductin f reserc ppers typiclly fllw te retricl pttern knwn s te crete--reserc-spce (r CARS) mdel in respnse t tw kinds f cmpetitin: cmpetitin fr reders nd cmpetitin fr reserc spce \citep{swles2004cdemic}. Mves in reserc pper intrductins:
\begin{enumerte}
    \item[Mve] 1 -- Estblis  reserc territry (wt s been dne)
        \begin{enumerte}[nsep]
            \item by swing tt te generl reserc re is imprtnt, centrl, interesting, prblemtic, r relevnt in sme wy (ptinl)
            \item by intrducing nd reviewing items f previus reserc in te re (bligtry)
        \end{enumerte}
    \item[Mve] 2 -- Estblis  nice ( nice is  cntext were  specific piece f reserc mkes prticulrly gd sense, tt is, te mtivtin fr te study)

        by indicting  gp in te previus reserc r by extending previus knwledge in sme wy (bligtry)
    \item[Mve] 3 -- Occupy te nice (wt te present reserc is but)
        \begin{enumerte}[nsep]
            \item by utlining purpses r stting te nture f te present reserc (bligtry)
            \item by listing reserc questins r ypteses (PISF = prbble in sme fields, but rre in ters)
            \item by nnuncing principl findings (PISF)
            \item by stting te vlue f te present reserc (PISF)
            \item by indicting te structure f te pper (PISF)
        \end{enumerte}
        Reviewers will nt even finis reding te pper if tere re mny tings wrng wit te pper. Fr exmples, lck f mtivtin, ld nd nt interesting prblem, pr Englis, te utrs swing lck f knwledge, pr metdlgy, flse clims, etc. In rder t effectively cmmunicte cntributins nd let reders clerly see te vlue f te prpsed metd nd wy tey suld use te metd, ll te clims suld be bcked up by quntittive dt, nlysis, nd cmprisn wit existing metds.
        
        Sufficient evidence swing te dvntges f te prpsed metd ver existing metds in te literture must be prvided. Differences nd imprvements fr metds nd results bsed n previusly publised nes suld be clerly described. Te grid cnvergence f te implementtins nd results must be demnstrted. Any deficits nd weknesses but te metd nd results suld nt be idden but suld be clerly nlyzed. D nt ver-generlize clims nd findings r intrduce tings tt re nt studied in te current wrk.
\end{enumerte}

\subsectin{Literture review}

A literture review is  cmpreensive exmintin f wt s been publised n  specific tpic by te resercers in tt field nd is usully ne f te first steps in reserc. Yu write literture reviews t identify trends, gps, intersectins, nd directins witin publised reserc wile ls situting yur wn wrk witin te lrger cntext by explining w yur wrk grew ut f erlier relted reserc nd detiling te mjr develpments in yur pprces. Yu use literture reviews t intrduce reders t te surrunding literture nd ls frm te bsis fr understnding te imprtnce f yur reserc.

Cnducting  literture review will elp yu t clrify yur understnding f te cntent, t criticlly pprise ter resercers' wrk, nd t estblis  cerent picture f te current bdy f knwledge, wic will rgnize yur tugts n nlyses f yur reserc nd stremline yur writing prcess. Writing  literture review requires summrizing, syntesizing, nlyzing, nd evluting.
\begin{figure}[!tbp]
    \centering
    \cptin{Anlyticl skills fr literture review.}
    \lbel{fig:review_skill}
\end{figure}

\prgrp{Frmt Vritins}

\emp{Stnd-lne literture reviews} re self-cntined pieces f writing tt cn summrize nd syntesize previusly publised studies n  specific tpic t utline existing evidence, t identify gps in current reserc, nd t psitin future reserc. Once resercers ve selected  tpic, te first step in teir reserc metdlgy is ften te stnd-lne literture review. \emp{Embedded literture reviews} re prt f  lrger piece f writing, suc s n essy, tesis, r sclrly rticle, fr discussing nd nlyzing publised mteril relted t te reserc tpic. Tey intrduce reders t te surrunding literture wile ls situting yur wrk witin te lrger sclrly discussin n tt tpic. Yu mke cler wt is yur wrk but nd ten explin crnlgiclly nd temticlly te imprtnt finds tt preceded nd mtivted yur reserc. Yu sw links between studies. Tis tigtly rgued sectin frms te bsis fr understnding te imprtnce f yur reserc.

\prgrp{Writing steps}
\begin{enumerte}
    \item Pre-writing
        \begin{enumerte}
            \item \emp{Plnning}: Cnstruct  reserc questin t direct yur reserc nd reding strtegies. Frm ere, identify te purpse r tesis fr yur tpic.
            \item \emp{Sercing}: Determine keywrds nd crefully select surces tt will prvide current nd credible infrmtin n yur tpic.
                \begin{enumerte}
                    \item First, use n cdemic serc engine suc s Ggle Sclr nd sme well-csen keywrds t find tree t five \emp{recent igly-cited} ppers in te re (srt by cittin t evlute qulity nd srt by dte t trck te reserc trends). Fr  cmplete new tpic, my use Wikipedi nd its reference list t find relevnt ppers. D ne-pss red n ec pper t get  sense f te wrk, ten red teir intrductin sectins. Yu will find  tumbnil summry f te recent wrk, nd perps, if yu re lucky,  pinter t  recent survey pper. If yu cn find suc  survey, yu re dne. Red te survey, cngrtulting yurself n yur gd luck.
                    \item Oterwise, in te secnd step f te tree-pss pprc, find sred cittins nd repeted utr nmes in te bibligrpy, r ceck igly-cited ppers in te cittin links f te pper prvided by te serc engine. Tese re te key ppers nd resercers in tt re. Dwnld te key ppers nd set tem side. Ten g t te websites f te key resercers nd see were tey've publised recently. Tt will elp yu identify te tp jurnls in tt field.
                    \item Te tird step is t use serc engine t serc te keywrds tgeter wit ec tp jurnl nme t identify recent ig-qulity relted wrk. Tese ppers, lng wit te nes yu set side erlier, cnstitute te first versin f yur survey. Mke tw psses trug tese ppers. If tey ll cite  key pper tt yu did nt find erlier, btin nd red it, iterting s necessry.
                \end{enumerte}
            \item \emp{Reding}: Literture reviews require  substntil munt f reding, s pprcing ec surce metdiclly results in  trug understnding f te cntent nd sves time. One strtegy fr ctive reding is t use te tree-pss metd \citep{kesv2007red} t brek yur reding int tree steps tt cllectively llw yu t quickly exmine ll spects f ec surce.
                \begin{enumerte}
                    \item First pss (quick scn t get  generl ide but te pper nd decide if yu need t red gin): crefully red te title, bstrct, nd intrductin $\t$ red te edings but ignre everyting else $\t$ glnce figures nd equtins t determine te underlying tereticl fundtins $\t$ red te cnclusins $\t$ glnce ver te references, mentlly ticking ff te nes yu've lredy red $\t$ determine te five Cs: Ctegry, te surce type suc s empiricl, tereticl, qulittive; Cntext, relted ppers nd teries; Crrectness, d te ssumptins pper t be vlid? Cntributins, te pper's min cntributins; Clrity, is te pper well written? Decide if yu will use te surce nd red gin.

                        Te first pss is dequte fr ppers tt ren't in yur reserc re, but my smedy prve relevnt. Incidentlly, wen yu write  pper, yu cn expect mst reviewers (nd reders) t mke nly ne pss ver it. Tke cre t cse cerent sectin nd sub-sectin titles nd t write cncise nd cmpreensive bstrcts, intrductin, nd cnclusins. If  reviewer cnnt understnd te gist fter ne pss, te pper will likely be rejected; if  reder cnnt understnd te igligts f te pper fter five minutes, te pper will likely never be red.

                    \item Secnd pss (grsp te cntent but nt its detils suc s prfs): Underline min ides/tesis/reserc questins. Mke digrms, flw crts, r utlines t represent min ides f prgrps. Summrize min ide f prgrps in yur wn wrds using ne sentence. Identify cnfusing sectins nd recrd relevnt unred references t return t fter furter reding. Summrize min findings. Determine te significnce f cnclusins. In te intrductin sectin f yur wn pper, write n verll summry f te surce t recrd utr's tesis, metdlgy, strengts, limittins, nd significnt findings in dditin t yur evlutin nd suggestins. In te reding prcess, extrct useful cntent nd stuff int te relted prts f yur wn pper.
                    \item Tird pss (finl red t fully understnd ssumptins nd vlidity f cnclusins): Identify nd cllenge every ssumptin nd cnclusin mde by te utrs. Recnstruct te study s if yu were te resercer t identify nt nly te pper's innvtins, but ls its idden filings nd ssumptins. Identify strengts nd weknesses f ides. Cnsider wt yu wuld d differently s te resercer. Recrd ides fr future wrk. In te intrductin f yur wn pper, refine te verll summry f te surce t reflect wt te pper is but, te min findings, nd yur evlutin f te pper, s if describing it t  friend, since te best wy t understnd smeting is t explin it t ters. Review yur summry t ensure yu ve nt missed vluble infrmtin.
                \end{enumerte}
        \end{enumerte}
    \item Drfting
        \begin{enumerte}
            \item \emp{Anlyzing}: Criticlly review ec surce's metds, prcedures, dt vlidity/relibility, nd ter temes f interest. Surces cn be rgnized crnlgiclly r temticlly. Orgnizing yur literture review ccrding t temes, metdlgies, nd underlying cncepts is mre effective tn listing ec surce ne by ne, s it demnstrtes yur mstery f te tpic nd prvides reders wit  better sense f te stte f reserc in tt field. Cnsider w ec surce pprces yur tpic in dditin t teir cllective pints f intersectin nd seprtin. Identify ny gps witin teir reserc. Try t plce yur current wrk nd reserc witin tis wider discussin by cnsidering w yur reserc supprts, cntrdicts, r deprts frm ter sclrs' reserc. Te key pint but literture reviews is tt tey suld clerly sw n rgnizing mind t wrk rter tn simple undigested lists f wt s been dne.

                Critique nd evlutin:
                \begin{itemize}[nsep]
                    \item Be fir nd resnble.
                    \item Use te sndwic metd: begin te critique wit psitive cmpliments, ten fllwed by cnstructive criticism (be brief yet cler nd elpful), ten ended by encurging suggestins r wises.
                    \item Be very cutius f evlutive lnguge, especilly negtive nes.
                    \item Use edging t sften pinins.
                    \item Use pst unrel cnditins (\emp{culd ve dne} r \emp{wuld ve been mre ... if d dne ...}) t express criticism regrding wt te utr suld ve dne but did nt d.
                \end{itemize}
            \item \emp{Syntesizing}: Syntesizing findings crss studies nd mke cnclusins bsed n te cllective evidence.
            \item \emp{Discussing}: Briefly explin te current stte f reserc but yur tpic. Use specific utrs r surces s exmples, nd be sure t explin ny similrities r deprtures in pprc, metdlgy, findings, r rgument. Ten, explin were yur reserc fits witin tis discussin nd wy yur wrk is useful.
        \end{enumerte}
    \item Revising
        \begin{enumerte}
            \item \emp{Revising}: Revise nd finlize te structure, style, infrmtin flw, nd grmmr, etc. 
        \end{enumerte}
\end{enumerte}

\sectin{Metd}

Describes, in vrius degree f detil, metdlgy, mterils (r subject), nd prcedures. Tis is te nrrwest prt f te reserc pper. Yu suld mke sure tt every metd described is relted t sme results nd ll results re relted t  metd.

A gd metdlgy leds t te expecttin tt te results will ls be gd. "If n bstrct is f interest, te editr next lks t te metds sectin f te mnuscript befre deciding weter t reject te pper r pss it n t te screening editr n duty fr tt dy. Te screen editr decides weter te mnuscript suld be sent fr externl review" -- E. Lngdn-Neuner

Fr ny reused metds prt, try t prprse te descriptins witut cpy verbtim. In generl, cpying text even frm ne f yur wn previusly publised rticles witut citing te surce is  brec f publictin etics s tis munts t self-plgirism. Similr t plgirism f nter persn's wrk, self-plgirism t, if detected fter publictin, culd led t retrctin. Editrs very rrely rely slely n plgirism detectin sftwre t give  mnuscript  verdict f plgirism. Editrs cnsider te sftwre results but lrgely use teir wn judgement s well. Editrs tend t be mre tlernt f textul similrities in te metds sectin, becuse mst riginl studies use previusly described metds. Hwever, te cnsensus is tt it is still essentil t cite te surce rticle in wic te metds were first described. Tis pplies even t cmmnly used metds.

Autrs w submit  mnuscript fr publictin cntining dt, reviews, cnclusins, etc., tt ve lredy been disseminted in sme significnt mnner (e.g., publised s n rticle in nter jurnl, presented t  cnference, psted n te internet) must clerly indicte t te editrs nd reders te nture f te previus dissemintin.

If yu re submitting tw mnuscripts bsed n te sme metd, ere's wt yu need t d t sfegurd yurself ginst self-plgirism:

1. Be sure tt te studies re distinct enug t wrrnt tw seprte publictins witut being cnsidered  cse f slmi slicing.

2. Ensure tt bt yur mnuscripts cite te riginl study tt first described te sid metd (ere, I ssume tt te metd itself s nt been devised by yu nd s been described previusly).

3. Infrm te editr in te cver letter tt te cntent duplictin in te metds sectin is intentinl s yu ve replicted  previusly publised metd.

4. If ne mnuscript gets publised erlier tn te ter, te secnd mnuscript suld cite te first nd indicte tt te metds ve been previusly described in ne f yur wn ppers.

5. If bt mnuscripts re submitted rund te sme time, te cver letter fr ec suld disclse tt nter study cnducted using te sme metd is under cnsidertin by nter jurnl.

6. Te mnuscript must g trug plgirism ceck first befre submissin.

\sectin{Results}

Te findings re described, ccmpnied by strng nd lgicl nlysis nd interprettins. If tere re ny drwbcks r insufficiency in te metds fr btining results, must d nt ide but suld clerly discuss te relted issues, ptentil cuses, nd influences. Every test cse nd result presented suld be interpreted, cnnected, nd cncluded clerly. Never let imptience tke ver nd let te reviewers r reders d te interprettin. Oterwise, tings will definitely g t te wrng directin nd cst  lt frm tt imptience nd lziness.

\sectin{Cnclusin}

Gives mening t nd interprets te results in  vriety f wys. Mke  series f slient "pints", t lest sme f wic refer t sttements mde in te intrductin. Te structure f discussin/cnclusin sectins:
\begin{enumerte}[nsep]
    \item[Mve] 1 -- Prviding bckgrund infrmtin (reserc purpses, tery, metdlgy) t cntextulize te study nd, in ding s, t cnslidte te reserc spce.
    \item[Mve] 2 -- Summrizing nd reprting key results
    \item[Mve] 3 -- Cmmenting n te key results (mking clims bcked up by quntittive dt, nlysis, nd cmprisn wit existing metds, explining te results, cmpring te new wrk wit te previus studies, ffering lterntive explntins, stting significnce fr te field f study)
    \item[Mve] 4 -- My cnsider mking recmmendtins fr future implementtin nd/r fr future reserc.
\end{enumerte}

\sectin{Revisin}

After finising te pper, it is recmmended t cmplete te fllwing tsks:
\begin{enumerte}
    \item \emp{A significnce nd nvelty sttement}: A cndensed intrductin t describe wt yur reserc is dding t te existing literture. Tis srt sttement suld ddress te nvelty spect nd te significnce f te wrk wit respect t te existing literture nd mre generlly t te sciety. Tis sttement suld be written t  brd udience, t n undergrdute level, nd limited t 120 wrds.

        Exmple:
        \lstinputlisting[lnguge=Tex]{Src/Significnce_nd_Nvelty.txt}


        Exmple:
        \lstinputlisting[lnguge=Tex]{Src/Higligts.txt}

    \item \emp{Cver letter}: Crft  well-written cver letter tt igligts te significnce nd nvelty f te reserc s well s prvides  gd resn wy te mnuscript is  gd fit fr te jurnl.
        \begin{enumerte}[nsep]
            \item Ceck weter te jurnl's "Instructins fr Autrs" ve ny cver letter requirements (e.g. disclsures, sttements, ptentil reviewers).
            \item Write  letter tt explins wy te editr wuld wnt t publis yur mnuscript:
                \begin{enumerte}[nsep]
                    \item If knwn, ddress te editr w will be ssessing yur mnuscript by nme. Include te dte f submissin nd te jurnl yu re submitting t.
                    \item First prgrp: Include te title nd te type f mnuscript (review, riginl rticle).
                    \item Secnd prgrp: Briefly explin te bckgrund f te study, te reserc questin sugt ut t nswer nd wy. Suld cncisely explin wt ws dne, te min findings nd wy tey re significnt.
                \end{enumerte}
        \end{enumerte}

        Exmple:
        \lstinputlisting[lnguge=Tex]{Src/Cver_Letter.txt}

    \item Prepre slides but te ides nd metds f te pper, give  presenttin t cllegues, nd slicit dvice. After revising te pper, put te pper side fr  cuple f dys r even lnger, ten reexmine te entire pper. Te mst criticl spect f revisin is tt ll cmments suld be vlued nd ddressed pint by pint wit quntittive dt nd nlysis.

\end{enumerte}

\subsectin{Respnding t te reviewer}

Yu my nt be ble t cntrl wt te reviewers write in teir review cmments, but yu cn cntrl te wy yu rect t teir cmments. It's useful t remember tese pints:

\prgrp{Reviewers ve, n te wle, given time nd effrt t cnstructively criticize yur rticle}

Reviewers re vlunteers nd ve given up teir wn time t evlute yur pper in rder t cntribute t te reserc cmmunity. Reviewers very rrely receive frml cmpenstin beynd recgnitin frm te editrs f te effrt tey ve expended. Te utr will get te ultimte credit, but reviewers re ften key cntributrs t te spe f te finl pper. Altug te cmments yu receive my feel rs, mst reviewers re ls utrs nd terefre will be trying t igligt w te pper culd be imprved. S, it is imprtnt t be grteful fr te time tt bt reviewers nd editrs ve spent evluting yur pper – nd t express tis grtitude in yur respnse.

\prgrp{Te imprtnce f gd mnners}

Yu suld remin plite nd tugtful trugut ny nd ll respnse t reviewers nd editrs. Yu re muc mre likely t receive  psitive respnse in return nd tis will elp build  cnstructive reltinsip wit bt reviewer nd editr in te future.

\prgrp{Dn't tke criticism s  persnl ttck}

As stted previusly, it is very rre tt  pper will be ccepted witut ny frm f revisins requested. It is te jb f te editr nd reviewer t mke sure tt te publised ppers re scientificlly sund, fctul, cler nd cmplete. In rder t cieve tis, it will be necessry t drw ttentin t res f imprvement. Wile tis my be difficult fr yu s n utr, te criticism received is nt intended t be persnl.

\prgrp{Avid persnlizing respnses t te reviewer}

Sticking t te fcts nd viding persnl ttcks is impertive. It's  gd ide t wit 24 t 72 urs befre respnding t  decisin letter, ten re-red te emil. Tis simple prcess will remve muc f te persnl bis tt culd pllute ppels letters written in rge r disppintment. If yu respnd in nger, r in n rgumenttive fsin te editr nd reviewers re muc less likely t respnd fvrbly.

Remember, even if yu tink te reviewer is wrng, tis desn't necessrily men tt yu re rigt! It is pssible tt te reviewer s mde  mistke, but it is ls pssible tt te reviewer ws nt ble t understnd yur pint becuse f  lck f clrity, r missin f crucil detil in yur pper.

\prgrp{Evluting te reviewer cmments nd plnning yur respnse}

After yu ve red te decisin letter nd te reviewers cmments, wit fr t lest 24 urs, ten tke  fres lk t te cmments prvided. Tis will elp t neutrlize te initil emtinl respnse yu my ve nd llw yu t determine wt te reviewers re sking fr in  mre bjective mnner.

Spending time ssessing te scpe f te revisins requested will elp yu evlute te extent f effrt required nd priritize te wrk yu my need t undertke. It will ls elp yu t prvide  cmpreensive respnse in yur letter f reply.

Sme useful steps t cnsider:
\begin{enumerte}
    \item Mke  list f ll te reviewer cmments nd number tem.
    \item Ctegrize te list s fllws:
        \begin{itemize}
            \item     requests fr clrifictin f existing text, dditin f text t fill  gp in te pper, r dditinl experimentl detils
            \item     requests t renlyze, re-express, r reinterpret existing dt.
            \item     requests fr dditinl experiments r furter prf f cncept.
            \item     requests yu simply cnnt meet.
        \end{itemize}
    \item Nte dwn te ctin/respnse tt yu pln t undertke fr ec cmment. If tere re requests tt yu cnnt meet, yu need t ddress tese in yur respnse – prviding  lgicl, resned explntin fr wy te study is nt detrimentlly ffected by nt mking te cnges requested.
    \item T let reviewers clerly see te vlidity f te respnse, ll te rguments nd clims in te pper s well s in te utr's respnse suld be bcked up by quntittive dt nd nlysis, viding nly use bstrct nd qulittive descriptin.
\end{enumerte}

\prgrp{Hw t ddress reviewers' cmments}

\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Answering plitely.} Never being insulting t te reviewers, te editr r te jurnl publisers; it is pintless nd unlikely t dvnce yur cse fr publictin.  Editrs d teir best t discurge inpprprite cmments by reviewers nd t edit ut ny tt tey my mke. If ny f tese t filter trug t yu ten d nt 'rise t te bit' nd reply in kind; stick t te pint tt is being rised.
    \item \textbf{Answering cmpletely.} Mens tw tings: respnding t ll te pints tt re rised; nd respnding t ec f te pints s trugly s yu cn.  Yur 'defult' setting ugt t be  willingness t mke ny necessry cnges but if tere re cntrdictry pints between reviewers nd/r  reviewer s ctully misunderstd yu r is ptently wrng, ten tese pints still need t be ddressed. Te wrst mistke yu cn mke is t ignre  pint. And, if yu re pinting ut n errr r  misunderstnding, ten refer t te pint bve but being plite.
    \item \textbf{Answering wit evidence.} Were yu disgree wit  reviewer yu must supprt tt wit evidence nd te best wy t d tis - prvided te evidence is crrect - is t reference ter publised wrk supprting yur pint.
    \item \textbf{Answering wit psitivity.} Be ptimistic nd prceed wit te belief tt if yu ddress te pints dequtely, ten yu re very likely t be ccepted nd publised.
\end{itemize}

\subsectin{Wt t d if yur mnuscript gets rejected}

It is very cmmn fr ppers t be rejected. Studies indicte tt $21\%$ f ppers re rejected witut review, nd pprximtely $40\%$ f ppers re rejected fter peer review.

\begin{enumerte}
    \item If yur pper s been rejected prir t peer review due t lck f subject fit, ten find  new jurnl t submit yur wrk t nd mve n.
    \item If yu receive  rejectin fter yur pper s been reviewed, yu will ve  ric surce f infrmtin but pssible imprvements tt yu culd mke. Yu suld mke cnges nd submit t  different jurnl.

        If yu decide t try  different jurnl, yu suld still crefully cnsider te cmments yu received during te first rund f review, nd wrk n imprving yur mnuscript befre submitting elsewere. Mke sure tt yu djust detils like te cver letter, referencing nd ny ter jurnl specific detils befre submitting t  different jurnl.
\end{enumerte}
